cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SI. 

The paper proposes a system for subjective knowledge acquisition using crowdsourcing, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of existing knowledge bases, which falls under the scope of cs.CY (computational complexity and cryptography). The paper also discusses the challenges of knowledge inference and resource constraints, which are relevant to cs.IR (information retrieval) and cs.SI (social and information networks).
